Question: d
Answer: prep. + abl., down from, from; concerning, about
Name: d

Question: in
Answer: prep. + abl., in, into, on, upon
Name: in

Question: propter
Answer: prep. + acc., on account of, because of
Name: propter

Question: sub
Answer: prep. + abl., (w/ verbs of rest), prep. + acc. (w/ verbs of motion), under, up under, close to; down to/into, to/at the foot of
Name: sub

Question: ad
Answer: prep. + acc., to, up to, near to in the sense of "place to which" with verbs of motion
Name: ad

Question: ex or
Answer: prep. + abl., out of, from, from within; by reason of, on account of
Name: ex or
